DataTypes:
   -->It specify the size and type of the value 
   -->two types
       1.Primitive DataTypes
       2.Non Primitive DataTypes

Primitive DataTypes:
  -->Size are already fixed
  -->Eight types (1 byte = 8 bit)
     1.byte  -1 byte
     2.short -2 byte
     3.int   -4 byte    
     4.long  -8 byte
     5.float -4 byte
     6.double-8 byte
     7.char  -2 byte
     8.boolean-1 bit
 
 Numerical     Decimal       Single      true/false
  Default      Default      Default      Default
  value-0       value-0.0   value-u000    value-false
  1.byte        1.float     Character      1.boolean
  2.short       2.double      1.char
  3.int
  4.long

Non Primitive DataTypes:
 -->Size is not fixed
 -->Four types    
    1.Array
    2.String (Default value-null)
    3.Class
    4.Interface

    Formula:
      -2^n-1 to (2^n-1)-1

      Ex:
      byte range:
      -2^8-1 to (2^8-1)-1
      -2^7 to (2^7)-1
      -128 to  127